80 to attend public school, Mrs. Gump.

74
00:08:14,703 --> 00:08:17,580
He's gonna have to go
to a special school.

75
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,790
Now, he'll be just fine.

76
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:22,668
What does "normal" mean, anyway?

77
00:08:22,752 --> 00:08:26,130
He might be a bit on the slow side,

78
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,008
but my boy Forrest is gonna get

79
00:08:29,092 --> 00:08:31,635
the same opportunities
as everyone else.

80
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:35,514
He's not going to some special school
to learn how to re-tread tires.

81
00:08:35,599 --> 00:08:38,767
We're talking about
five little points here.

82
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:43,105
There must be something can be done.

83
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:47,151
We're a progressive school system.

84
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:50,905
We don't want to see anybody
left behind.

85
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:55,242
Is there a Mr. Gump, Mrs. Gump?

86
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:00,372
He's on vacation.

87
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:21,644
Well, your mama sure does care
about your schooling, son.

88
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:29,610
You don't say much, do you?

89
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:43,082
"Finally, he had to try.

90
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,125
"It looked easy, but,

91
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:48,671
"oh, what happened.

92
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:51,757
-"First, there..."
-Mama, what's "vacation" mean?

93
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,885
-Vacation?
-Where Daddy went.

94
00:09:57,514 --> 00:10:00,224
Vacation's when you go somewhere

95
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,937
and you don't ever come back.

96
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:13,070
Anyway, I guess you could say
me and Mama was on our own.

97
00:10:14,281 --> 00:10:17,908
But we didn't mind.
Our house was never empty.

98
00:10:17,993 --> 00:10:20,577
There was always folks
coming and going.

99
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:21,745
Supper.

100
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:25,249
-It's supper, everyone. Forrest...
-My, my. That sure looks special.

101
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,876
Sometimes we had
so many people staying with us

102
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:30,629
that every room
was filled with travelers.

103
00:10:30,714 --> 00:10:34,341
You know, folks living out
of their suitcases

104
00:10:34,426 --> 00:10:37,386
and hat cases and sample cases.

105
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:40,889
Forrest Gump, it's suppertime!
Forrest...

106
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:43,517
One time, a young man
was staying with us,

107
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:47,229
and he had him a guitar case.

108
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:05,205
Forrest! I told you not to bother
this nice young man.

109
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,623
Oh, no, that's all right, ma'am.

110
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,543
I was just showing him a thing or two
on the guitar here.

111
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:12,588
All right, but your supper's ready
if y'all want to eat.

112
00:11:12,672 --> 00:11:15,632
Yeah, that sounds good.
Thank you, ma'am.

113
00:11:16,301 --> 00:11:19,887
Say, man, show me that crazy
little walk you just did there.

114
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:21,847
Slow it down some.

115
00:11:23,975 --> 00:11:25,893
I liked that guitar.

116
00:11:26,561 --> 00:11:28,312
It sounded good.

117
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:34,276
I started moving around to the music,

118
00:11:34,361 --> 00:11:36,195
swinging my hips.

119
00:11:38,782 --> 00:11:41,325
This one night,
me and Mama was out shopping,

120
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:44,411
and we walked right by
Benson's furniture and appliance store,

121
00:11:44,496 --> 00:11:46,080
and guess what?

122
00:11:58,426 --> 00:12:01,261
This is not for children's eyes.

123
00:12:03,807 --> 00:12:05,599
Some years later,
that handsome young man

124
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:08,227
who they called "The King,"

125
00:12:08,311 --> 00:12:10,646
well, he'd sung too many songs,

126
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:13,857
had himself a heart attack,
or something.

127
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:17,111
Must be hard being a king.

128
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:24,243
You know, it's funny how you remember
some things, but some things you can't.

129
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:28,872
-You do your very best now, Forrest.
-I sure will, Mama.

130
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:35,170
I remember the bus ride
on the first day of school very well.

131
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:40,426
Are you coming along?

132
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:44,012
Mama said not to be taking
rides from strangers.

133
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,265
This is the bus to school.

134
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:51,478
I'm Forrest. Forrest Gump.

135
00:12:52,439 --> 00:12:56,442
-I'm Dorothy Harris.
-Well, now we ain't strangers anymore.

136
00:13:09,456 --> 00:13:11,248
This seat's taken.

137
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,210
It's taken!

138
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:24,970
You can't sit here.

139
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:30,559
You know, it's funny what
a young man recollects,

140
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,020
'cause I don't remember being born.

141
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:36,815
I don't recall what I got
for my first Christmas,

142
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:39,985
and I don't know when I went
on my first outdoor picnic.

143
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:44,781
But I do remember the first time I heard

144
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:47,701
the sweetest voice in the wide world.

145
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:50,579
You can sit here if you want.

146
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:57,377
I had never seen anything
so beautiful in my life.

147
00:13:58,087 --> 00:14:00,172
She was like an angel.

148
00:14:00,256 --> 00:14:03,175
Well, are you gonna sit down,
or aren't you?

149
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:09,932
What's wrong with your legs?

150
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:14,269
Nothing at all, thank you.
My legs are just fine and dandy.

151
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:17,356
I just sat next to her on that bus

152
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,525
and had a conversation
all the way to school.

153
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:22,319
...my back's crooked like
a question mark.

154
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:23,570
These are going to make me...

155
00:14:23,655 --> 00:14:28,408
And next to Mama, no one ever
talked to me or asked me questions.

156
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:30,911
Are you stupid or something?

157
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:33,997
Mama says, "Stupid is as stupid does."

158
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:39,294
-I'm Jenny.
-I'm Forrest. Forrest Gump.

159
00:14:39,963 --> 00:14:41,797
From that day on,
we was always together.

160
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:44,716
Jenny and me was like
peas and carrots.

161
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,930
She taught me how to climb.

162
00:14:50,014 --> 00:14:52,724
Come on, Forrest, you can do it.

163
00:14:52,809 --> 00:14:55,435
I showed her how to dangle.

164
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,563
"...a good little monkey and..."

165
00:14:57,647 --> 00:15:02,568
She helped me learn how to read,
and I showed her how to swing.

166
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:08,657
Sometimes we'd just sit out
and wait for the stars.

167
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:13,662
-Mama's gonna worry about me.
-Just stay a little longer.

168
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:18,667
For some reason,
Jenny didn't never want to go home.

169
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:20,836
Okay, Jenny, I'll stay.

170
00:15:21,671 --> 00:15:24,423
She was my most special friend.

171
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:29,511
My only friend.

172
00:15:33,308 --> 00:15:37,102
Now, my mama always told me that
miracles happen every day.

173
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,563
Some people don't think so, but they do.

174
00:15:42,609 --> 00:15:44,192
Hey, dummy!

175
00:15:45,153 --> 00:15:47,237
