I gotta get out of here.

492
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,185
Wait, Jenny...

493
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:19,732
Forrest, you stay away from me, okay?
You just stay away from me, please.

494
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:21,108
Can I have a ride?

495
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:22,735
-Where you going?
-I don't care.

496
00:39:22,819 --> 00:39:24,194
Get in the truck.

497
00:39:24,279 --> 00:39:26,113
So, bye-bye, Jenny.

498
00:39:28,616 --> 00:39:30,951
They sending me to Vietnam.

499
00:39:33,705 --> 00:39:36,123
It's this whole other country.

500
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:40,627
Just hang on a minute.

501
00:39:42,047 --> 00:39:45,090
Listen, you promise me
something, okay?

502
00:39:45,175 --> 00:39:48,510
Just, if you're ever in trouble,
don't try to be brave. You just run, okay?

503
00:39:48,636 --> 00:39:50,220
Just run away.

504
00:39:51,473 --> 00:39:52,806
Okay.

505
00:39:57,687 --> 00:39:59,021
Jenny.

506
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:03,192
I'll write you all the time.

507
00:40:12,327 --> 00:40:15,329
And just like that, she was gone.

508
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:34,765
You come back safe to me,
do you hear?

509
00:41:18,059 --> 00:41:22,020
Now, they told us that Vietnam
was gonna be very different

510
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:24,982
from the United States of America.

511
00:41:25,066 --> 00:41:30,112
And except for all the beer cans
and the barbecue, it was.

512
00:41:40,248 --> 00:41:43,333
Hey, I bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

513
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:46,587
They tell me these Vietnams
are good shrimpers.

514
00:41:46,671 --> 00:41:50,215
You know, after we win this war,
and we take over everything,

515
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:51,508
we can get American shrimpers

516
00:41:51,593 --> 00:41:53,343
to come out here
and shrimp these waters.

517
00:41:53,428 --> 00:41:54,970
We'll just shrimp all the time, man.

518
00:41:55,096 --> 00:41:58,265
So much shrimp, why,
you wouldn't believe it.

519
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:00,851
You must be my FNGs.

520
00:42:00,935 --> 00:42:02,186
-Morning, sir!
-Morning, sir!

521
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:04,897
Get your hands down! Do not salute me.

522
00:42:04,981 --> 00:42:07,107
There's goddamn snipers
all around this area

523
00:42:07,192 --> 00:42:10,027
who would love to grease an officer.

524
00:42:10,111 --> 00:42:13,614
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fourth Platoon.

525
00:42:14,490 --> 00:42:16,909
What's wrong with your lip?

526
00:42:16,993 --> 00:42:19,369
I was born with big gums, sir.

527
00:42:19,454 --> 00:42:24,166
Yeah, well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

528
00:42:25,335 --> 00:42:26,710
Where you boys from in the world?

529
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:29,171
-Alabama, sir!
-Alabama, sir!

530
00:42:29,881 --> 00:42:31,381
You twins?

531
00:42:33,468 --> 00:42:35,886
No, we are not relations, sir.

532
00:42:38,139 --> 00:42:41,058
Look, it's pretty basic here.

533
00:42:41,851 --> 00:42:44,311
lf you stick with me
and learn from the guys

534
00:42:44,395 --> 00:42:47,064
who've been in country a while,
you'll be all right.

535
00:42:47,148 --> 00:42:49,066
There is one item of GI gear

536
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:53,320
that can be the difference between
a live grunt and a dead grunt.

537
00:42:53,655 --> 00:42:56,823
Socks. Cushion sole, OD green.

538
00:42:56,908 --> 00:42:58,200
Try and keep your feet dry.

539
00:42:58,326 --> 00:42:59,743
When we're out humping,
I want you boys to remember

540
00:42:59,827 --> 00:43:02,287
to change your socks
whenever we stop.

541
00:43:02,372 --> 00:43:05,332
The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet
right off his legs.

542
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:07,709
Sergeant Sims, God damn it,

543
00:43:07,835 --> 00:43:09,253
where is that sling rope
I told you to order?

544
00:43:09,337 --> 00:43:11,255
I put in the requisitions at Battalion.

545
00:43:11,339 --> 00:43:13,340
Yeah, yeah, yeah, well,
you call those sons of bitches again...

546
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:18,345
Lieutenant Dan sure knew his stuff.
I felt real lucky he was my lieutenant.

547
00:43:19,097 --> 00:43:22,557
He was from a long,
great military tradition.

548
00:43:22,767 --> 00:43:25,852
Somebody in his family
had fought and died

549
00:43:26,854 --> 00:43:31,108
in every single American war.

550
00:43:32,026 --> 00:43:34,027
-God damn it, kick some ass!
-I'm on it, Lieutenant.

551
00:43:34,112 --> 00:43:35,237
Get on it!

552
00:43:35,363 --> 00:43:38,699
I guess you could say he had
a lot to live up to.

553
00:43:40,410 --> 00:43:45,247
So, you boys are from Arkansas, huh?
Well, I've been through there.

554
00:43:45,373 --> 00:43:47,541
Little Rock's a fine town.

555
00:43:48,209 --> 00:43:51,795
Now, go shake down your gear,
see the platoon sergeant,

556
00:43:51,879 --> 00:43:54,339
draw what you need for the field.

557
00:43:54,424 --> 00:43:58,385
lf you boys are hungry,
we got steaks burning right over here.

558
00:43:58,469 --> 00:44:01,346
Two standing orders in this platoon:

559
00:44:01,431 --> 00:44:04,099
one, take good care of your feet,

560
00:44:04,225 --> 00:44:09,271
two, try not to do anything stupid,
like getting yourself killed.

561
00:44:15,737 --> 00:44:17,821
I sure hope I don't let him down.

562
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:34,338
I got to see a lot of the countryside.
We would take these real long walks.

563
00:44:42,805 --> 00:44:46,933
And we were always looking
for this guy named Charlie.

564
00:44:54,776 --> 00:44:57,027
-Hold it up!
-Hold up, boys!

565
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:02,199
It wasn't always fun.

566
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:06,578
Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings about a rock,

567
00:45:06,662 --> 00:45:11,750
or a trail, or the road,
so he'd tell us to get down, shut up...

568
00:45:11,834 --> 00:45:13,835
Get down! Shut up!

569
00:45:14,796 --> 00:45:16,254
...so we did.

570
00:45:33,815 --> 00:45:35,982
Now, I don't know much about anything,

571
00:45:36,067 --> 00:45:39,903
but I think some of America's
best young men served in this war.

572
00:45:39,987 --> 00:45:42,697
There was Dallas, from Phoenix,

573
00:45:44,409 --> 00:45:47,202
Cleveland, he was from Detroit.

574
00:45:47,328 --> 00:45:49,704
Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

575
00:45:49,831 --> 00:45:51,998
Man, what the hell's going on?

576
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:56,420
And Tex was... Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from.

577
00:45:56,504 --> 00:45:58,046
Nothing.

578
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:04,678
Fourth Platoon, on your feet.

579
00:46:04,762 --> 00:46:08,473
Still got 10 clicks to go to that river.
Move out.

580
00:46:08,558 --> 00:46:10,350
Come on, move out.

581
00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,813
Step it up. Look alive out there.

582
00:46:14,897 --> 00:46:19,234
The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always some place to go.

583
00:46:19,360 --> 00:46:20,735
Fire in the hole!

584
00:46:24,198 --> 00:46:26,533
Gump, check out that hole.

585
00:46:26,617 --> 00:46:29,619
And there was always something to do.

586
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:32,873
-Mount them up.
-Spread out! Cover his back.

587
00:46:37,920 --> 00:46:43,550
One day, it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.

588
00:46:44,552 --> 00:46:47,429
We'd been through
every kind of rain there is:

589
00:46:47,555 --> 00:46:50,098
little bitty stinging rain,

590
00:46:50,808 --> 00:46:53,477
and big old fat rain,

591
00:46:53,936 --> 00:46:56,646
rain that flew in sideways.

592
00:46:56,731 --> 00:47:00,775
And sometimes, rain even seemed
to come straight up from underneath.

593
00:47:02,570 --> 00:47:04,946
Shoot, it even rained at night.

594
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,450
-Hey, Forrest.
-Hey, Bubba.

595
00:47:08,576 --> 00:47:11,870
I'm gonna lean up against you.
You just lean right back against me.

596
00:47:11,954 --> 00:47:15,790
This way, we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

597
00:47:16,751 --> 00:47:20,212
You know why we a good partnership,
Forrest?

598
00:47:20,296 --> 00:47:22,797
'Cause we be watching out
for one another,

599
00:47:22,924 --> 00:47:24,799
like brothers and stuff.

600
00:47:26,761 --> 00:47:30,430
Hey, Forrest, there's something
I've been thinking about.

601
00:47:30,515 --> 00:47:33,517
I got a very important question
to ask you.

602
00:47:35,144 --> 00:47:39,105
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

603
00:47:40,274 --> 00:47:41,900
Okay.

604
00:47:41,984 --> 00:47:45,445
Man, I tell you what,
I got it all figured out, too.

605
00:47:45,530 --> 00:47:48,323
So many pounds of shrimp
to pay off the boat,

606
00:47:48,449 --> 00:47:51,743
so many pounds for gas,
we can just live right on the boat.

607
00:47:51,827 --> 00:47:54,120
We ain't got to pay no rent.

608
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:56,289
I'll be the captain,
we can just work it together,

609
00:47:56,374 --> 00:48:00,627
split everything right down the middle.
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

610
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:04,297
And, hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

611
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:07,634
That's a fine idea.

612
00:48:08,719 --> 00:48:10,845
Bubba did have a fine idea.

613
00:48:14,642 --> 00:48:17,727
I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

614
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:21,731
I sent her letters,
not every day, but almost.

615
00:48:21,816 --> 00:48:26,820
I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

616
00:48:26,904 --> 00:48:29,656
and told her
how I thought about her always,

617
00:48:30,992 --> 00:48:33,952
and how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

618
00:48:34,036 --> 00:48:36,538
just as soon as she had the time.

619
00:48:38,416 --> 00:48:40,917
I'd always let her know that I was okay.

620
00:48:42,211 --> 00:48:47,382
Then, I'd sign each letter,
"Love, Forrest Gump."

621
00:49:02,231 --> 00:49:05,984
This one day, we was out walking,
like always,

622
00:49:06,068 --> 00:49:09,029
and then, just like that,

623
00:49:09,947 --> 00:49:13,366
somebody turned off the rain
and the sun come out.

624
00:49:16,370 --> 00:49:18,204
Ambush!

625
00:49:18,706 --> 00:49:20,081
Take cover!

626
00:49:23,711 --> 00:49:24,878
Get down!

627
00:49:24,962 --> 00:49:26,421
Get the sixty!

628
00:49:29,592 --> 00:49:31,676
Get that pig up here, God damn it!

629
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,887
Forrest, you okay?

630
00:49:37,099 --> 00:49:39,726
Strongarm! Strongarm!
Be advised, Strongarm!

631
00:49:40,269 --> 00:49:42,687
Medic, we got a man down!

632
00:49:42,772 --> 00:49:45,732
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6, over!

633
00:49:46,442 --> 00:49:49,778
Roger, Strongarm, be advised
we have incoming from the tree line

634
00:49:49,904 --> 00:49:53,406
at points blue plus two.
AKs and rockets...

635
00:49:54,075 --> 00:49:55,867
Misfire! Misfire!

636
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,246
God damn it! Mac!

637
00:50:01,207 --> 00:50:04,626
Get that thing...
Fuck it, get it in the tree line!

638
00:50:05,586 --> 00:50:06,753
Jesus!

639
00:50:06,879 --> 00:50:09,089
My unit is down hard and hurting!

640
00:50:09,215 --> 00:50:12,759
Six are pulling back to Blue Line,
Leg Lima 6 out.

641
00:50:13,552 --> 00:50:15,512
Pull back! Pull back!

642
00:50:15,596 --> 00:50:17,722
Run! Run, Forrest!

643
00:50:17,807 --> 00:50:20,141
-Pull back!
-Forrest, Forrest!

644
00:50:20,267 --> 00:50:22,852
Run, man! Run!

645
00:50:22,937 --> 00:50:24,729
Pull back! Run!

646
00:50:26,565 --> 00:50:28,775
Run, God damn it, run!

647
00:50:49,964 --> 00:50:54,592
Medic! Can I get a medic?

648
00:50:54,969 --> 00:50:58,304
I ran and ran, just like Jenny told me to.

649
00:51:01,684 --> 00:51:05,895
I ran so far and so fast
that pretty soon I was all by myself,

650
00:51:05,980 --> 00:51:07,939
which was a bad thing.

651
00:51:08,482 --> 00:51:10,024
Bubba!

652
00:51:12,153 --> 00:51:15,947
Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure that he was okay.

653
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:21,703
Any friendlies out there?

654
00:51:22,663 --> 00:51:24,831
Yeah, I've got three over here.

655
00:51:25,458 --> 00:51:27,459
Where the hell are you?

656
00:51:28,043 --> 00:51:29,377
Bubba?

657
00:51:30,463 --> 00:51:33,173
And on my way back to find Bubba,

658
00:51:33,299 --> 00:51:36,092
well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.

659
00:51:36,177 --> 00:51:37,385
Tex!

660
00:51:39,472 --> 00:51:40,472
Okay.

661
00:51:40,556 --> 00:51:44,517
I couldn't just let him lay there all alone,
scared the way he was,

662
00:51:44,643 --> 00:51:48,521
so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

663
00:52:03,662 --> 00:52:06,080
And every time I went back
looking for Bubba,

664
00:52:06,207 --> 00:52:09,709
somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest. Help me."

665
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:19,260
Can't hear... Can't hear...

666
00:52:21,555 --> 00:52:22,847
No sweat, man. Just lay back.

667
00:52:22,932 --> 00:52:25,433
You'll be okay. You'll be okay.

668
00:52:27,436 --> 00:52:30,480
I started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.

669
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:31,815
...over.

670
00:52:31,899 --> 00:52:35,193
Roger, Strongarm,
I know my position is danger close.

671
00:52:35,277 --> 00:52:37,111
We got Charlie all over this area.

672
00:52:37,238 --> 00:52:39,531
I gotta have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

673
00:52:39,615 --> 00:52:42,992
-Six, Strongarm, we want...
-Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

674
00:52:43,077 --> 00:52:44,285
I know he's dead!

675
00:52:44,411 --> 00:52:47,247
My whole goddamn platoon
is wiped out!

676
00:52:47,373 --> 00:52:48,706
-Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6.
-God damn it!

677
00:52:48,791 --> 00:52:51,501
-Copy this transmission. Over.
-What are you doing?

678
00:52:51,585 --> 00:52:54,921
Just leave me here! Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

679
00:52:55,047 --> 00:52:57,340
Leg Lima 6, Strongarm.
How copy this? Over.

680
00:52:57,424 --> 00:53:00,051
God, I said leave me here, God damn it!

681
00:53:00,135 --> 00:53:03,304
Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6,
this is Strongarm, be advised

682
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:05,390
your fast movers
are inbound at this time, over.

683
00:53:05,474 --> 00:53:08,893
Then, it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.

684
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:11,437
Something bit me!

685
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,446
You chink son of a bitch!

686
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:24,951
I can't leave the platoon.

687
00:53:25,077 --> 00:53:29,998
I told you to leave me there, Gump.
Forget about me. Get yourself out!

688
00:53:30,124 --> 00:53:32,250
Did you hear what I said?

689
00:53:32,960 --> 00:53:34,919
God damn it, put me down!

690
00:53:35,629 --> 00:53:37,672
Get your ass out of here!

691
00:53:40,968 --> 00:53:43,553
I didn't ask you to pull me out of there,
God damn you!

692
00:53:43,637 --> 00:53:44,971
Where the hell
do you think you're going?

693
00:53:45,097 --> 00:53:46,180
To get Bubba.

694
00:53:46,307 --> 00:53:50,143
I got an air strike inbound right now.
They're gonna nape the whole area.

695
00:53:50,269 --> 00:53:52,645
Gump, you stay here, God damn it!
That's an order!

696
00:53:52,771 --> 00:53:55,189
I gotta find Bubba!

697
00:54:11,165 --> 00:54:12,624
Forrest.

698
00:54:20,382 --> 00:54:23,051
-Bubba.
-I'm okay, Forrest.

699
00:54:23,844 --> 00:54:25,511
I'm okay.

700
00:54:33,354 --> 00:54:35,188
Oh, Bubba, no...

701
00:54:35,314 --> 00:54:37,523
Nah, I'm gonna be all right.

702
00:54:45,699 --> 00:54:48,368
Come on. Come on. Come on.

703
00:54:53,374 --> 00:54:54,874
I'm okay, Forrest.

704
00:54:56,210 --> 00:54:59,045
I'm okay, man. I'm fine.

705
00:55:36,083 --> 00:55:39,210
Helo's inbound.
Top smoke, get it out there!

706
00:55:40,254 --> 00:55:44,757
lf I'd a known this was gonna be the
last time me and Bubba was gonna talk,

707
00:55:44,883 --> 00:55:47,176
I'd of thought of something better to say.

708
00:55:47,261 --> 00:55:48,761
Hey, Bubba.

709
00:55:49,888 --> 00:55:51,264
Hey, Forrest.

710
00:55:53,600 --> 00:55:56,811
Forrest, why'd this happen?

711
00:55:58,147 --> 00:55:59,939
You got shot.

712
00:56:01,650 --> 00:56:05,820
Then Bubba said something
I won't ever forget.

713
00:56:06,613 --> 00:56:08,281
I wanna go home.

714
00:56:10,284 --> 00:56:12,326
Bubba was my best good friend.

715
00:56:13,287 --> 00:56:17,832
And even I know that ain't something
you can find just around the corner.

716
00:56:17,958 --> 00:56:21,044
Bubba was gonna be
a shrimping boat captain,

717
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:25,089
but instead he died right there
by that river in Vietnam.

718
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:33,097
That's all I have to say about that.

719
00:56:35,476 --> 00:56:37,643
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

720
00:56:39,980 --> 00:56:42,648
-A bullet?
-That jumped up and bit you.

721
00:56:45,027 --> 00:56:47,111
Oh, yes, sir.

722
00:56:47,196 --> 00:56:50,323
Bit me directly in the buttocks.

723
00:56:50,449 --> 00:56:55,703
They said it was a million-dollar wound,
but the Army must keep that money,

724
00:56:55,829 --> 00:56:59,665
'cause I still ain't seen a nickel
of that million dollars.

725
00:57:00,501 --> 00:57:04,003
The only good thing
about being wounded in the buttocks

726
00:57:04,129 --> 00:57:05,838
is the ice cream.

727
00:57:05,964 --> 00:57:08,549
They gave me all the ice cream
I could eat.

728
00:57:08,675 --> 00:57:09,967
And guess what?

729
00:57:10,052 --> 00:57:13,179
A good friend of mine
was in the bed right next door.

730
00:57:15,390 --> 00:57:18,476
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

731
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:23,022
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream.

732
00:57:34,743 --> 00:57:37,036
It's time for your bath, Lieutenant.

733
00:57:45,546 --> 00:57:46,879
Harper!

734
00:57:50,092 --> 00:57:52,552
Cooper, Larson,

735
00:57:54,763 --> 00:57:56,097
Webster,

736
00:57:57,516 --> 00:58:01,018
-Gump. Gump.
